        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>How to Compress PDF Files</h2>
            <p>Our free PDF compressor makes it easy to reduce PDF file size while maintaining quality. Follow these simple steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Upload your PDF</strong> by dragging and dropping or clicking the upload area</li>
                <li><strong>Select compression level</strong> - choose between low, medium, high, or extreme compression</li>
                <li><strong>Choose optimization target</strong> - web, email, print, or archival</li>
                <li><strong>Click "Compress PDF"</strong> and wait a few seconds</li>
                <li><strong>Download</strong> your optimized PDF file</li>
            </ol>
            
            <h3>Why Compress PDF Files?</h3>
            <p>PDF compression is essential for:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Email attachments:</strong> Many email servers have size limits for attachments</li>
                <li><strong>Website uploads:</strong> Smaller files load faster for your visitors</li>
                <li><strong>Storage savings:</strong> Reduce space used by large PDF collections</li>
                <li><strong>Faster sharing:</strong> Compressed files transfer quicker over networks</li>
                <li><strong>Mobile access:</strong> Smaller files use less data on mobile devices</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>How Our PDF Compression Works</h3>
            <p>Our tool uses advanced algorithms to reduce PDF file size through several optimization techniques:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Image compression:</strong> Optimizes embedded images without visible quality loss</li>
                <li><strong>Font subsetting:</strong> Includes only used characters from embedded fonts</li>
                <li><strong>Metadata removal:</strong> Strips unnecessary metadata and comments</li>
                <li><strong>Object optimization:</strong> Reorganizes PDF internal structure for efficiency</li>
                <li><strong>Stream compression:</strong> Applies advanced compression to PDF data streams</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
